premise_source_doc_sentence: Many issues include obituaries of relevant scholars .
These public places that distribute the newspaper include grocery stores , civic centers , libraries , restaurants , and retail stores .
Other prominent news events covered by the newspaper include the Woodstock '94 music festival and the marijuana arrests  (  in 2004 and 2005  )  of singer Art Garfunkel .
Previous editors of the newspaper include Paua Manu'atu  (  Tuisoso  )  , Mateaki Heimuli , Feleti Tu'ihalamaka , Kalafi Moala , Josephine Latu-Sanft and Tevita Motulalo .
Notable alumni of the newspaper include Bloomberg Businessweek reporter Cam Simpson , Associated Press national editor Chris Sundheim , and several Pulitzer Prize winners .
